      <hedline>
        <hl1>The View From Wilkes-Barre</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Chuck Cohen letter concerns Feb 4 article on US economy</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>In ''How to Fix the Economy Without Even Touching It'' (On the Contrary, Feb. 4), Daniel Akst discussed energy policy, among other issues. He said that ''sacrificing the environment for more cheap oil won't seem like such a good idea when the greenhouse effect turns Wilkes-Barre, Pa., into oceanfront property.'' As a resident of northeastern Pennsylvania, I ask: So, do you see something wrong with that?</p>
        <p>CHUCK COHEN  Wilkes-Barre, Pa., Feb. 5</p>
      </block>
